er Guru could not independently verify the authenticity of the Bitcoin holder.4:[["$","header",null,{"className":"site-header","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"container","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"header-inner","children":[["$","$Ld",null,{"href":"/","className":"header-brand","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"header-logo","children":"C"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"header-text","children":[["$","h1",null,{"children":["Cryptonews",["$","span",null,{"children":".in.th"}]]}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Crypto Intelligence Aggregator"}]]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"header-status","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"status-dot"}],["$","span",null,{"children":"Live Feed Active"}]]}]]}]}]}],["$","$Le",null,{"article":{"_id":"6985c2cd38f2116917ca015d","guid":"https://coinpedia.org/?p=541884","__v":0,"author":"Nidhi Kolhapur","categories":["bitcoin"],"category":"bitcoin","content":"The post Bitcoin Crash Triggers Biggest One-Day Investor Losses in History appeared first on Coinpedia Fintech News\nBitcoin’s recent fall has triggered one of the biggest loss-taking events in its history, illustrating how quickly market sentiment has shifted after months of strong gains. As prices dropped nearly 10% to around $64,000, Bitcoin hit its lowest level since late 2024. This sharp move pushed many investors to sell their holdings at a loss. …","createdAt":"2026-02-06T10:30:37.295Z","enclosure":"https://image.coinpedia.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/13154400/US-CPI-Data-Release-Today-Will-Bitcoin-Price-Surge-Above-92K-or-Drop-Below-90K-1-1024x536.webp","fetchedAt":"2026-02-06T10:30:37.295Z","link":"https://coinpedia.org/news/bitcoin-crash-triggers-biggest-one-day-investor-losses-in-history/","pubDate":"2026-02-06T10:16:24.000Z","sentiment":"bearish","source":"Coinpedia","sourceCategory":"general","summary":"","title":"Bitcoin Crash Triggers Biggest One-Day Investor Losses in History","translatedContent":"โพสต์ Bitcoin พังทลายทำให้นักลงทุนข